The paper proposes a deep multi-agent reinforcement learning framework for autonomous air traffic control, which involves decision-making in a highly dynamic and stochastic environment. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also deals with safety-critical decision-making in a complex system, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. The use of a centralized learning, decentralized execution scheme and the evaluation of the model through simulations suggest that the paper could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the paper deals with multi-agent reinforcement learning, which could fall under the Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) category.
